image.altText: A New Zealand player in black head butts a white ball while fending off a Norwegian player dressed in white.

items.synopsis: The biggest tournament in women's football is here as Australia and New Zealand welcome the globe to the FIFA Women's World Cup. Follow the action from day 1 with the ABC's live blog.

title.children: Matildas and New Zealand launch home World Cup

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A fantastic piece of play! A fantastic ball played to Jacqui Hand down the right touchline followed by the perfect cross to Hannah Wilkinson. She was unmarked, she couldn't miss. She didn't miss.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: GOAL NEW ZEALAND

children.content: A fantastic ball played to Jacqui Hand down the right touchline followed by the perfect cross to Hannah Wilkinson.
She was unmarked, she couldn't miss. She didn't miss.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Can New Zealand convert their dominance into a goal? Can Norway show their class? We are under way!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: The players return to the pitch for the second half

children.content: Can New Zealand convert their dominance into a goal?

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Norway looked set to score. Caroline Graham Hansen flew down the right wing and played a lovely ball into the box, at the feet of Ada Hegerberg. Only desperate diving defence from New Zealand's back-four prevented their goalkeeper Victoria Esson needing to make a save. Norway are starting to warm into the contest again.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 40': Great defence keeps the scores level

children.content: Caroline Graham Hansen flew down the right wing and played a lovely ball into the box, at the feet of Ada Hegerberg.
Only desperate diving defence from New Zealand's back-four prevented their goalkeeper Victoria Esson needing to make a save.
Norway are starting to warm into the contest again.
